(1749, 1, '2013-07-26 19:14:27', '2013-07-26 19:14:27', '<span style="text-align: justify; display: block;"><a href="FaithFarmCorporate/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faith_farm_bridge.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1790 alignright" alt="faith_farm_bridge" src="FaithFarmCorporate/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faith_farm_bridge-300x226.png" width="300" height="226" /></a>We are happy to announce that the bridge renovation project at our Boynton Beach location is underway. Thanks to the generous support of many we are now able to begin this project. Our bridge is the only ingress/egress for campus traffic: Faith Farm''s Thrift Store, Customers, Staff and Program Residents, Faith Farm trucks picking up or making deliveries and vendors. The property is surrounded by canals on all sides. Deterioration of the bridge is occurring on a constant basis due to it''s age, volume of traffic and increased loads. Recent X-rays of the bridge show that existing joists do not have the steel reinforcements to support the truck traffic at the current span. Structural Engineers have approved a twelve month usage span structural bracing with crutch bents (steel supports) under the bridge which will maintain the safety of the bridge. The Boynton Beach Thrift Store provides 60% of the organization''s funds supporting the Men''s and Women''s free recovery program as well as the location for the Ministry Administrative Office, Celebrate Recovery and a Polling facility. No Capital funds are available but a new bridge must be built at a cost of $1,140,000. All funds raised will be allocated to "Save Our Bridge" without any offset for fundraising or administrative fees.</span>', 'Boynton Beach Bridge Project Underway!!!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1-autosave', '', '', '2013-07-26 19:14:27', '2013-07-26 19:14:27', '', 1, 'FaithFarmCorporate/?p=1749', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
